Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.62,0:00:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Child of a Hero
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.93,0:00:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother will die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.11,0:00:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She said she wanted to return to her hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:00:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,NOVEMBER 1013 AD\NWESSEX, SOUTH OF ENGLAND
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.96,0:02:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our main army\Ndefeated the resistance at Wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.84,0:02:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It is only a matter of time until we conquer the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If all goes well, everything will be done before winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.85,0:02:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to London?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.65,0:02:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And Canute,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.74,0:02:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.32,0:03:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The besieging army that Canute was leading\Nwas attacked by Thorkell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't heard anything since.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard rumors they engaged in battle at Marlborough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible they joined the local soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.59,0:03:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we are not yet sure\Nwhether they got away safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.43,0:03:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He's my dear son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.80,0:03:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as you find out more, tell me immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.39,0:03:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.20,0:03:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We're surrounded!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.20,0:03:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.04,0:03:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,See? I told you so!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:03:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.21,0:03:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, men!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.46,0:04:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen well! Don't return fire. Don't touch them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.97,0:04:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Messengers of Brycheiniog!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.81,0:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What a rough welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So you speak our language, you barbarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that you Danes were just like beasts\Nthat can't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Withdraw your troops, Asser.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.32,0:04:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Making trouble with the Danes\Nis of no benefit to Wales.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.28,0:04:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratianus!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.79,0:04:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect your concern\Nfor the future of the kingdoms of Wales.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But our values are different from yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.59,0:04:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What promise are you trying to make\Nwith the prince of the Danes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.39,0:04:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just barbarians! They have no morals!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What is he shouting about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.85,0:04:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we going to fight or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.73,0:04:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No. This isn't going to turn into a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what he's saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.32,0:05:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.86,0:05:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But they could have killed one of us with their first shot\Nif they wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.61,0:05:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They were trying to intimidate us
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they could control the negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.95,0:05:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You beasts!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.88,0:05:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched your war with England closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.09,0:05:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You entered three cease-fire agreements\Nin the last ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and violated them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.01,0:05:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not make the same foolish mistake as England!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall capture the prince and use him as a shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.27,0:05:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the king of the devils\Nmust still love his own child!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.57,0:05:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Askeladd.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.78,0:05:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's just an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just making trouble to see how we'll respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These days, a sheep must wear a wolf's skin to graze.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:05:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sympathy for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to tell them about your plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but if they want to put up an act,\NI can go along with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.85,0:06:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Look closely!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The man standing here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.36,0:06:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is none other than the son of King Sweyn of Denmark,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,His Highness Canute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,His Highness will now address you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Be silent and listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.83,0:06:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, Your Highness. Say something spirited.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be anything. Like, "I'm going to boil you\Nalive and eat you."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.67,0:06:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Make those rude scoundrels uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If it comes from you, their balls will shrink\Nand they'll let us through.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,His Highness dislikes talking in front of other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall do it instead--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.70,0:07:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He may be young, but he's still a prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.29,0:07:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He has responsibilities he must live up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone standing here now
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is acting for the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.30,0:07:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a gentle person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't like unnecessary fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.22,0:07:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm asking him to do this.\NTo avoid an unnecessary fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think you can handle succeeding
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.86,0:07:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,King Sweyn with your mouth clamped up like a clam?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.65,0:07:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You could never understand His Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.37,0:07:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The palace is a fox nest where parents, children,\Nand siblings eat each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.91,0:08:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea how hard it was for\Nthe frail and sickly prince to survive through that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He silenced his heart, silenced his breath,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and made sure he didn't stand out.\NThat's how he survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.72,0:08:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And even after all that, he's still approached
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.80,0:08:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by bastards like you who want to use him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.48,0:08:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't step out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.73,0:08:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your place to try to control how he acts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you arguing about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.71,0:08:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Canute say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratianus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.67,0:08:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to tell them the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.80,0:08:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. I shall go too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.68,0:09:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys! Wait right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go talk to their leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.94,0:09:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.86,0:09:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was worried about the prince,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.15,0:09:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and ended up overstepping my bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness, please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.10,0:09:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You loser. Are you really the same age as me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:09:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That man is named Ragnar, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.87,0:10:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.37,0:10:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know that fledglings all leave\Nthe nest someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What he's doing is actually bad for the chick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.75,0:10:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many things you have to do\Nto put your plan in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is to make the chick leave the nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.69,0:10:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay back. I don't need any guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.94,0:10:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.15,0:10:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make me say it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.15,0:10:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It would bring shame to our king if they thought\NI can't talk without guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.62,0:10:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,More! Get five times further away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.34,0:10:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the others too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.01,0:11:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You said your name was Askeladd, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand your situation,\Nbut you're putting me in a hard spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that he's already agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking for permission for passage\Nthrough our country and supplies for your men.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't agree immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.69,0:11:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be small, but our king also has a reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in it for us if we help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to confirm that this is a transaction between\Ntwo parties of equal standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.92,0:11:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Or else my men will think that the king is scared\Nof only 100 Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't look good for you\Nif you just agreed to our demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for not showing more consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.02,0:11:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who wrote the letter to your country.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.48,0:11:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I wrote in the letter that I can't give details
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.15,0:11:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about your reward\Nin order to maintain secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I read that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.11,0:12:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then may I ask about that secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.79,0:12:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on the reward I offer you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,would you consider joining us in the war, Asser?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.84,0:12:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that a small country like us
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.30,0:12:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is no match for the king of Denmark!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.43,0:12:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me. I was just checking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.19,0:12:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a weird guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-Who?\N-Askeladd, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know he could speak Welsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.33,0:12:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess there's some things even you don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.83,0:12:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot. There's lots I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:13:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All I know is that he's from Denmark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.76,0:13:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's such a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.72,0:13:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been together for decades,\Nbut he never tells me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sulking about it? I thought you're a grown man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.35,0:13:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! Are you trying to start a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.02,0:13:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.56,0:13:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares? He's a good leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.69,0:13:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And luck is on his side.\NAs long as he lets me make money,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care where he's from. I'll follow him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.04,0:13:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.42,0:13:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's too unbelievable to be a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's Lydia's child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd has inherited the blood of the great leaders\Nof the Roman Celts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're not a Dane?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm of mixed Danish and Welsh blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My father Olaf conquered the coast of Wales\Nin the past
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.69,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and carried away Lydia as his concubine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.61,0:14:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was their child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I had heard that the bloodline of the war gods\Nof Old Britannia had gone extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.58,0:14:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying you're a descendant of Artorius?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.92,0:14:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Artorius
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was the commander of the Britannia army,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.43,0:14:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a country of native Celtic inhabitants of England
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.55,0:14:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the fifth and sixth centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.27,0:14:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In 516,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.06,0:14:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,he defeated the invading Saxons
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.48,0:14:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the English
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.86,0:14:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Battle of Baden Hill
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.73,0:14:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought peace to Britannia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.78,0:14:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Legends about him were passed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.74,0:14:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the person that the legend of King Arthur\Nwas based on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any proof
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.04,0:15:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of your story?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.09,0:15:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.34,0:15:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was 14,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he visited Wales with Lydia and met me for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.06,0:15:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She was an unlucky person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She was kept in my father's bedroom for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,After she became sick, she was kept in the stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.28,0:15:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.57,0:15:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But who would ever imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that the last remaining survivor of the great bloodline
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is mixed with Danish blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.66,0:15:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly it, Asser.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because I'm of mixed blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I blend in with the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Wales is going to have
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.26,0:15:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,an insider in the army of Denmark, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:16:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can make that rich boy into the next king of Denmark,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.73,0:16:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then I can claim a high position too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.02,0:16:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.61,0:16:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can conclude a treaty of non-aggression with Wales.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let them...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.41,0:16:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,take even one step into this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness! That's so bold!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.05,0:16:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You almost had me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.76,0:16:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-Asser is laughing.\N-He's confident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.27,0:16:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I have one concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.61,0:16:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You were raised among the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.98,0:16:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure the blood of Artorius is stronger\Nthan the blood of the Danes within you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll just have to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of my blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.59,0:17:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.84,0:17:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your swords here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.55,0:17:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll give them back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.77,0:17:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.31,0:17:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let go of my weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just pretending to be their prisoners
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.61,0:17:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,while we pass through their country.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.57,0:17:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll return our weapons when we get to the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.45,0:17:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That way they won't lose face.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.45,0:17:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's strange.\NWhy do your men follow your orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.79,0:17:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because my men trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.22,0:17:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Thorfinn. You too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.26,0:17:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mess with me, baldy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You said trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.93,0:18:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He's different. You damn kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get the wrong idea, conehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not one of his men. I'm an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.90,0:18:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,An enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.90,0:18:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. So be it. You two don't have to obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only the two of you. I'm sure they'll allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Let's start marching again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.08,0:18:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Danes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.46,0:18:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard Asser captured them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-I heard they eat humans!\N-They look evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Asser is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me try throwing a stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.69,0:18:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.86,0:18:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They piss me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.44,0:18:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They're treating us like animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You better not look at us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to eat you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.13,0:19:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't look, princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.63,0:19:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's something you want to say,\Nsay it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.09,0:19:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you have a tongue?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.18,0:19:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.44,0:19:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.94,0:19:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I don't talk isn't because\NI'm a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.90,0:19:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I-- I'm cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.95,0:19:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to be cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm different from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My words have political repercussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:20:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in a foreign country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Without permission from my father, the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.01,0:20:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't enter a treaty of non-aggression,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or say words to make them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.73,0:20:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad for an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.45,0:20:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like you're smart enough, princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.62,0:20:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.54,0:20:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.58,0:20:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's treated me like this before!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.46,0:20:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it was a good experience, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.88,0:20:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it back! It's not an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.30,0:20:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand how hard it is to be\Nfrom the royal family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.05,0:20:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop barking. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not barking!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.35,0:20:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just declaring that I'm right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.64,0:20:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.31,0:20:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with your attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe His Highness is talking to someone\Nother than me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.69,0:21:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not your servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.70,0:21:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd! Can't you go any faster?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.71,0:22:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be trapped in the snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.63,0:22:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough already. He's such a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.01,0:22:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to cross the northern edge of Mercia
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.97,0:22:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and head for the main army in Gainsborough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.89,0:22:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll arrive in one week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.14,0:22:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean we'll go through enemy territory?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.98,0:22:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get trapped in the mountains of Wales in the snow,\Nwe'll be stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.65,0:22:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.53,0:22:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We're far away from the enemy's main camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.78,0:22:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But how are you going to get supplies?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.49,0:22:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The lords in the countryside aren't going to\Nhelp out a Dane!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.41,0:22:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.29,0:22:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've thought about that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.42,0:22:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Men! We're changing directions! With haste!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.30,0:22:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.05,0:22:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We're changing routes all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.30,0:22:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry! Askeladd's decision isn't wrong!
